opean, North American and Australian cases and dynamics, going beyond common regional limitations of discussions on international migration or multiculturalismAddresses a cross-disciplinary readership including law, political science, sociology and political theoryContributorsRainer Bauböck, European University Institute, ItalyJozefien De Bock, Gent University, BelgiumBouke de Vries, Max Planck Institute for the Study of Religious and Ethnic Diversity, GermanyMatteo Gianni, University of Geneva, SwitzerlandGeoffrey Brahm Levey, University of New South Wales, AustraliaEdward Koning, University of Guelph, CanadaWill Kymlicka, Queen’s University, CanadaSune Lægaard Philosophy, Roskilde University, DenmarkPeggy Levitt, Harvard University, USATariq Modood, University of Bristol, UKJustyna Salamońska, University of Warsaw, PolandAnna Triandafyllidou, European University Institute, Italy  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCitizenship. 0aEmigration and immigration. 0aForeign workers. 0aMulticulturalism. 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aBader, Veit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanting, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauböck, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrahm Levey, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Bock, Jozefien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGianni, Matteo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoning, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKymlicka, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevitt, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLægaa